21:54.133 --> 21:56.533
so we wanted to leave you
with a happy story,

21:56.533 --> 21:58.300
and it involves Bolivia,

21:58.300 --> 21:59.934
a country you think about
so little,

21:59.934 --> 22:02.367
you don't even realize
that's not Bolivia;

22:02.367 --> 22:04.767
that's Colombia,
except it isn't.

22:04.767 --> 22:06.467
That's Venezuela.

22:06.467 --> 22:08.533
That is Colombia,
except it isn't.

22:08.533 --> 22:10.567
That's Bolivia, which is the one
we were looking for

22:10.567 --> 22:11.667
in the first place.

22:11.667 --> 22:13.000
Which one's Colombia?

22:13.000 --> 22:16.333
There is simply no way to know.

22:16.333 --> 22:19.834
The point is,
the Bolivian city of La Paz

22:19.834 --> 22:21.834
has had longstanding problems
with their roads,

22:21.834 --> 22:23.000
including traffic jams

22:23.000 --> 22:24.834
and a high rate
of fatal accidents.

22:24.834 --> 22:27.400
And I know that you're thinking,
"Wait. Hold on.

22:27.400 --> 22:28.934
"Your happy story

22:28.934 --> 22:31.533
involves fatal car accidents
in Bolivia?"

22:31.533 --> 22:32.734
Well, wait. Wait.

22:32.734 --> 22:34.734
Wait. Trust me.

22:34.734 --> 22:37.567
Because this is the solution
they came up with.

22:37.567 --> 22:38.967
[reporter speaking Spanish]

22:38.967 --> 22:40.900
- Appropriating the image
of the crosswalks,

22:40.900 --> 22:42.467
called "zebras,"

22:42.467 --> 22:45.467
and dressed in a costume
of the animal by the same name,

22:45.467 --> 22:47.867
these young people have been
going into the street

22:47.867 --> 22:51.300
of the city of La Paz
for the past 13 years

22:51.300 --> 22:53.900
with the goal of educating
the citizens with love

22:53.900 --> 22:55.667
and changing the chaotic face

22:55.667 --> 22:58.066
of the vehicular traffic
in this city.

22:58.066 --> 23:01.500
- Admit it.
You didn't see that coming.

23:01.500 --> 23:03.734
Not a single one of you

23:03.734 --> 23:06.033
was sitting there going,
"Traffic zebras!

23:06.033 --> 23:07.033
"I'm calling it!

23:07.033 --> 23:10.133
Traffic zebras! Yes!"

23:10.133 --> 23:13.300
Now, these zebras
don't have policing powers,

23:13.300 --> 23:15.767
like the ability to issue
tickets or make arrests.

23:15.767 --> 23:17.967
Instead,
they just tease people.

23:17.967 --> 23:19.100
And if you look online--

23:19.100 --> 23:21.600
and I cannot recommend
you do that enough--

23:21.600 --> 23:24.333
there is incredible footage
of them in action.

23:24.333 --> 23:27.000
You can see everything
from a zebra holding his head

23:27.000 --> 23:28.834
while a man jaywalks

23:28.834 --> 23:30.500
to one dancing
and spinning around

23:30.500 --> 23:32.133
in front of a speeding van
that stops

23:32.133 --> 23:33.967
just in the nick of time

23:33.967 --> 23:37.700
to this zebra risking his life
to stop a car

23:37.700 --> 23:40.133
to the many, many clips
of zebras dancing,

23:40.133 --> 23:43.467
every single one of which,
especially the last one,

23:43.467 --> 23:46.300
is absolutely superb.

23:46.300 --> 23:48.500
Watch him throw that down.

23:48.500 --> 23:50.700
And at this point,
you may be wondering,

23:50.700 --> 23:52.900
how did this happen?

23:52.900 --> 23:56.200
Well, it was based on
a similar program in Colombia,

23:56.200 --> 23:58.533
uh, where they dispatched
traffic mimes

23:58.533 --> 24:00.066
to monitor pedestrians.

24:00.066 --> 24:02.567
And as far as having mimes
rove around your city,

24:02.567 --> 24:05.734
I think we can all agree:
No.

24:05.734 --> 24:07.900
Not only is it
tremendously unpleasant,

24:07.900 --> 24:10.400
but being mocked by a mime
doesn't even work.

24:10.400 --> 24:13.266
All you have to say is,
"I can talk, and you can't."

24:13.266 --> 24:14.600
Argument won.

24:14.600 --> 24:17.467
You lock him in a glass box,
and you walk away.

24:17.467 --> 24:20.300
But Bolivia has really
taken it up a notch

24:20.300 --> 24:22.000
with this whole zebra business.

24:22.000 --> 24:24.767
The program started
with just 24 of them,

24:24.767 --> 24:28.700
and today in La Paz alone,
there are 265.

24:28.700 --> 24:30.633
That is a population boom
so great,

24:30.633 --> 24:32.734
it puts actual zebras
to shame.

24:32.734 --> 24:34.266
And that is saying something

24:34.266 --> 24:37.000
because zebras notoriously
have no shame.

24:37.000 --> 24:40.467
Put it away!
Put it away!

24:40.467 --> 24:42.667
That thing is a liability.

24:42.667 --> 24:44.200
Tuck it away.

24:46.233 --> 24:49.700
And while it may look like fun
for people,

24:49.700 --> 24:53.266
this is a real job
with strict rules.

24:53.266 --> 24:54.467
[reporter speaking Spanish]

24:54.467 --> 24:55.834
- They explained
some of the rules

24:55.834 --> 24:58.667
to be zebras, like:
honor the costume,

24:58.667 --> 25:00.333
don't eat when you work,

25:00.333 --> 25:03.200
never, never
take your head off.

25:03.200 --> 25:04.467
