Never take your head off.

25:05.934 --> 25:08.600
You cannot risk shattering
an innocent child's belief

25:08.600 --> 25:11.667
that you are a real free-roaming
bipedal talking equid

25:11.667 --> 25:13.967
6,000 miles from Africa.

25:13.967 --> 25:16.734
And by the way, that applies
even in interview situations.

25:16.734 --> 25:18.567
There are many, many clips

25:18.567 --> 25:22.266
of reporters shoving
microphones in zebras' faces,

25:22.266 --> 25:26.533
even one with a zebra giving
an interview to another zebra.

25:26.533 --> 25:28.533
- This is very significant
for me.

25:28.533 --> 25:30.133
I really like what I'm doing,

25:30.133 --> 25:32.633
and it's not just about
telling people what to do.

25:32.633 --> 25:34.300
- Come on!

25:34.300 --> 25:37.300
Every interview is improved
by a zebra head.

25:37.300 --> 25:39.266
There's a lesson for everyone
there.

25:39.266 --> 25:41.367
Stressful interview
with "60 Minutes"?

25:41.367 --> 25:43.266
Put on a zebra head.

25:43.266 --> 25:45.033
Tough questions
on the red carpet?

25:45.033 --> 25:47.000
You put on a zebra head.

25:47.000 --> 25:48.066
Sean Spicer?

25:48.066 --> 25:50.066
Get yourself a zebra head,
man.

25:50.066 --> 25:51.567
What is wrong with you?

25:51.567 --> 25:52.600
[cheers and applause]

25:52.600 --> 25:54.867
And--and here's the thing.

25:54.867 --> 25:57.400
It doesn't just help
with Bolivia's traffic.

25:57.400 --> 25:58.934
Many of the people
in those costumes

25:58.934 --> 26:00.934
really need the work.

26:00.934 --> 26:02.767
- Many of the zebras
are young people

26:02.767 --> 26:05.867
who are recovering
drug addicts and alcoholics.

26:05.867 --> 26:08.533
It's a way for them to get
their lives back on track

26:08.533 --> 26:11.166
and to give something back
to society.

26:11.166 --> 26:15.000
- Look, they're not only
getting their lives on track.

26:15.000 --> 26:17.166
I'm pretty sure
the existence of these zebras

26:17.166 --> 26:21.066
is the only thing keeping
my life on track right now.

26:21.066 --> 26:23.900
And is it any wonder
how beloved these cebritas  are,

26:23.900 --> 26:26.867
considering the attitude
that they project?

26:26.867 --> 26:28.700
- Oh!
- Cebrita!

26:30.367 --> 26:33.300
- [speaking Spanish]

26:37.367 --> 26:40.834
- Yes, the zebra was inside her
the whole time,

26:40.834 --> 26:42.767
which, admittedly,
sounds like a description

26:42.767 --> 26:45.100
for a very risqué YouTube video,
but that's not the point.

26:45.100 --> 26:47.467
The point is,
I've got a few questions here.

26:47.467 --> 26:49.567
First: How the hell

26:49.567 --> 26:52.734
did no one
tell me about this before?

26:52.734 --> 26:55.133
I feel like we've been
pretty clear on this show

26:55.133 --> 26:57.066
about our interest
in South American countries

26:57.066 --> 26:59.066
you have scant
geographical knowledge of

26:59.066 --> 27:01.734
and people in animal costumes.

27:01.734 --> 27:04.066
And frankly,
I have needed this

27:04.066 --> 27:05.867
over the last few months.

27:05.867 --> 27:07.633
The news has been hard.

27:07.633 --> 27:09.967
Which brings me
to my second question.

27:09.967 --> 27:12.700
If zebras can make
Bolivian traffic jams bearable,

27:12.700 --> 27:14.700
what else could they help with?

27:14.700 --> 27:16.567
So here is what we've done.

27:16.567 --> 27:19.233
We made our own Bolivian zebra

27:19.233 --> 27:20.834
and have been seeing
if they can help

27:20.834 --> 27:22.500
make painful moments
easier to take.

27:22.500 --> 27:23.834
And I'll show you how it works.

27:23.834 --> 27:25.567
Remember Trump's inauguration?

27:25.567 --> 27:27.734
Tough to watch, right?
But I'll say this.

27:27.734 --> 27:31.166
It's a lot easier to watch
with a zebra involved.

27:31.166 --> 27:34.200
- I, Donald John Trump,
do solemnly swear...

27:34.200 --> 27:38.133
- I, Donald John Trump,
do solemnly swear...

27:38.133 --> 27:40.667
- That I will faithfully
execute...

27:40.667 --> 27:43.166
- That I will faithfully
execute...

27:43.166 --> 27:46.200
- The office of President
of the United States.

27:46.200 --> 27:49.834
- The office of President
of the United States.

27:49.834 --> 27:52.533
- See?
It's better, right?

27:52.533 --> 27:54.867
Again,
it doesn't change anything,

27:54.867 --> 27:56.934
but it is easier to watch.

27:56.934 --> 27:59.133
Now, this works for
moments of frustration too.

27:59.133 --> 28:00.800
Remember how it felt
on Tuesday night

28:00.800 --> 28:02.400
when Rachel Maddow
made you sit through

28:02.400 --> 28:03.800
19 minutes of preamble

28:03.800 --> 28:06.233
to get to what amounted
to very nearly nothing?

28:06.233 --> 28:08.233
Well, you know
what could have helped then?

28:08.233 --> 28:10.633
A zebra to share your pain.

28:10.633 --> 28:11.767
- Somebody...

28:11.767 --> 28:13.767
[pages rustling]

28:13.767 --> 28:16.400
Has decided to leak...

28:16.400 --> 28:19.400
A portion
of his 2005 tax return,

28:19.400 --> 28:23.100
which is how and why
we got it tonight.

28:23.100 --> 28:26.100
And I am sure
it is only the start,

28:26.100 --> 28:27.467
but it's a start,

28:27.467 --> 28:30.000
and our little piece of it,

28:30.000 --> 28:31.834
we just got it.

28:31.834 --> 28:33.166
We'll go through it, next.

28:33.166 --> 28:35.066
- Come on!

28:35.066 --> 28:37.467
- I promise,
it works for anything.

28:37.467 --> 28:39.734
Take "Manchester by the Sea."

28:39.734 --> 28:41.333
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

28:41.333 --> 28:43.100
Pretty harrowing movie,
right?

28:43.100 --> 28:45.066
That couple went through hell.

28:45.066 --> 28:47.767
You know, if only
they weren't so alone.

28:49.367 --> 28:50.300
- [sniffs]

28:50.300 --> 28:51.934
Maybe you don't want
to talk to me.

28:51.934 --> 28:52.934
- [mutters]

28:52.934 --> 28:55.767
- No, let me finish.

28:55.767 --> 28:59.467
I love you.

28:59.467 --> 29:01.500
My heart was broken.

29:04.333 --> 29:06.367
It's always gonna be broken.

29:08.533 --> 29:10.967
And I know
yours is broken too.

29:13.166 --> 29:15.600
- Look, look, I think it's--

29:15.600 --> 29:16.600
[cheers and applause]

29:16.600 --> 29:18.633
I think it's pretty clear.

29:18.633 --> 29:21.133
With things in America
the way they are now,

29:21.133 --> 29:24.100
we need these zebras
like never before.

29:24.100 --> 29:26.266
And that is why
we've uploaded footage

29:26.266 --> 29:27.600
of a green screen zebra

29:27.600 --> 29:30.100
going through
a wide variety of emotions.

29:30.100 --> 29:31.867
You can use them
however you want.

29:31.867 --> 29:33.533
Just let us know
whatever you did

29:33.533 --> 29:35.800
with the hashtag
#JUSTADDZEBRAS.

29:35.800 --> 29:37.834
That is our show.
Thank you so much for watching.

29:37.834 --> 29:39.667
We'll be off next week,
back April 2nd.

29:39.667 --> 29:40.834
Good night.

29:40.834 --> 29:43.600
Please enjoy a dancing zebra!

29:43.600 --> 29:46.600
[cheers and applause]

29:46.600 --> 29:49.600
[upbeat dance music]

29:49.600 --> 29:56.533
♪ ♪

29:59.967 --> 30:01.900
[bright tone]
